org.naomi.regex

Enum CoreBuiltIn

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CoreBuiltIn>
      • org.naomi.regex.CoreBuiltIn
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<CoreBuiltIn>, BuiltInInterface

    public enum CoreBuiltIn
extends Enum<CoreBuiltIn>
implements BuiltInInterface
    This Enum defines a set of constants, each of which specifies a pre-defined "Core" set of characters to be matched (as described below). Each of these Enum constants can be used to instantiate a BuiltInCharClass that matches any of the characters in the corresponding pre-defined set. For example, 

        Pattern digits = new BuiltInCharClass(CoreBuiltIn.digit);
    matches (on each repetition) any single digit character, whereas 

        Pattern patternAny = new BuiltInCharClass(CoreBuiltIn.anyButLineEnds);
    matches (on each repetition) any single character that is not a line terminator.
